node.text:
Here’s the truth about “FDA Approved”:

There’s a BIG misconception that the FDA diligently reviews and approves new ingredients before we start eating them. 

Sadly this isn’t the case. 

New ingredients are usually approved by the food manufacturer themselves, and NOT by the FDA. 

All an ingredient manufacturer has to do is HIRE THEIR OWN EXPERTS to claim it’s safe. This is the green light to start adding it to food products.

Several “FDA Approved” products have been yanked from the shelves after they were found to be downright dangerous. 

But this doesn’t happen overnight. 

History shows that it takes YEARS before the FDA acts and removes harmful products from the market. 

Something very serious needs to happen – like deaths – before the FDA takes action. And even then, they may not.

Remember how Johnson & Johnson’s talc powder was recently removed from the shelves after slews of cancer claims and cover-ups by the company?

Well, the FDA didn’t ban it. 

J&J voluntarily decided to stop selling it to stop lawsuits from piling up.

Meanwhile, this controversial ingredient is banned in Europe. 

This just goes to show how little the FDA has done to protect our health. 

Tag your friends below to spread the word!

Even though we’ve made tremendous progress…the truth is that big companies just don’t change fast enough.

I believe we deserve to live in a world where our products can be made without weird – and nasty – ingredients.

Is that too much to ask?

Apparently so. Because we are so far away it’s crazy.

So, I decided to take matters into my own hands.

I launched @truvani and we have one main goal: eliminate nasty ingredients from all daily-use products.

We started with supplements. Now we are creating personal care products. 

Visit Truvani.com to learn more.

I know you’ll like them. And when you see the ingredient labels, you’ll LOVE THEM.

node.text:
If you feel like you don’t have the power to get food companies to drop nasty chemical ingredients from their food, I have news for you! Every time you share the truth about food products with your friends you are making a huge difference. Food companies are listening and they are changing. 

Years ago, I called Ghirardelli out for using the controversial conservative TBHQ in their chocolate squares, which has been shown to harm the immune system and is linked to other health issues, such as increasing the risk of food allergies to nuts, milk, eggs, wheat, and shellfish.

Ghirardelli recently replaced TBHQ with “extracts of oregano, flaxseed, plum, and green tea”. They also removed artificial flavors and several preservatives. 

I believe this never would have happened had we not shared the truth about their products and raised awareness!

Three more brands who have recently changed, after I wrote about them in Feeding You Lies: 

1. Pepsico removed brominated vegetable oil (BVO) from Mountain Dew. This ingredient is BANNED in Europe, which is why they sold it in other countries without it for years. 

2. Kellogg’s dropped the controversial preservative BHT (which is linked to cancer) from Frosted Flakes, so it’s now like the version they sell in other countries.

3. Quaker removed the artificial colors from their instant oatmeals and now use real fruit. 

So, keep sharing the truth about our food.

We are making a real difference! The #FoodBabeArmy is AMAZING. I love you all so much.

P.S. Ghirardelli still uses corn syrup and natural flavors - and they are not organic - so this isn’t a brand that I personally buy. My favorite chocolate brands are Hu and Alter Eco.

This is one of the tricky food labels that I discuss in my book, Food Babe Kitchen. 

“Multigrain” sounds healthy, but probably doesn’t mean what you think it does.

This simply means that multiple types of grains are used in the product. These grains may be refined into a flour, and therefore stripped of their nutrients and healthy fiber.

Like most breads, Nature’s Own Multigrain Bread is mostly made with refined wheat flour, sugar, and unhealthy soybean oil. 

These ingredients increase inflammation in the body, which can lead to obesity, heart disease, type 2 diabetes, and other diseases over time.

Since it’s not organic, it potentially contains residues of synthetic pesticides like glyphosate (Roundup). This weed killer is strongly linked to cancer. 

So, how do you choose healthy bread? Check out the last post in my feed for my favorite brands and some tips for choosing good brands. 

Please tag your friends below to share. I wish I knew this information sooner than I did!

It’s time to talk about one of the most wonderful and satisfying foods on earth – Bread! I don’t want to live without it and you shouldn’t have to either.

My diet consists mostly of plants like fruits, vegetables, seeds, beans and nuts...and I like bread on occasion, but only if it’s organic and made with nutrient-dense whole grains, sprouts, and seeds.

Swipe left to see more of my picks! 

Here’s what you need to know about conventional bread: 

✔️Wheat is commonly sprayed with Roundup weed killer at harvest - a chemical strongly linked to cancer. This practice is banned on organic crops.

✔️When conventional wheat is turned into flour, it can be treated with any of the 60 different chemicals approved by the FDA before it ends up on store shelves – including chemical bleach! This industrial processing destroys nutrients, such as Vitamin E and fiber.

✔️Wheat crops in this country have been through some serious manipulation to make them profitable for the food industry and less healthy for us.

✔️Most store bought breads are full of ingredients that are not food, like dough conditioners and preservatives. It only takes 4 ingredients to make bread – flour, yeast, water and salt, there’s really no need for all that other nonsense.

✔️ High fructose corn syrup is a heavily processed sweetener made from Roundup-Ready GMO cornstarch that contains more fructose than regular corn syrup.

✔️ Studies have shown it increases appetite and the risk of weight gain, type 2 diabetes, heart disease, cancer and dementia. HFCS particularly contributes to type 2 diabetes in children.

✔️ One study also found it can be contaminated with toxic mercury.

Eating processed refined sugars like this definitely isn’t something to take lightly. 

Our kids are being bombarded with high fructose corn syrup, and as you can see, it’s not just in candy and sodas.

node.text:
Adding this summertime recipe to the menu this week! This garden-fresh salad is refreshing and makes an incredible light lunch. You can store the dressing and prepped ingredients in your fridge, so it’s super easy to assemble for lunch on busy days. It also packs well, just make sure you keep the dressing on the side until you’re ready to eat! Feel free to swap the almonds for a nut or seed of choice. Sunflower seeds would be good. 

Tag your friends below to share this healthy real food recipe! 

You’ll find more salad recipes like this in my cookbook, Food Babe Kitchen. It’s available at FoodBabeKitchen.com

Food Babe’s Strawberry Crunch Salad
(Makes 2 to 3 servings)

Ingredients:
2 cups mixed greens
2 cups baby spinach or arugula
1 cup sliced strawberries
1 avocado, peeled and diced
½ cucumber, thinly sliced
3 radishes, thinly sliced
¼ cup sliced almonds
¼ cup goat feta cheese

Vinaigrette:
¼ cup extra virgin olive oil
3 tablespoons apple cider vinegar
2 teaspoons raw honey
1 teaspoon dijon mustard
1 shallot, diced
Sea salt and ground black pepper

Directions:
1. Place all of the salad ingredients in a bowl and toss to combine.
2. To make the vinaigrette, whisk together ingredients. Pour over salad and serve.

Buying fermented pickles at the store is pretty expensive, but the good news is that making fermented pickles at home is SUPER EASY more affordable.
 
I have the recipe inside my cookbook, Food Babe Kitchen (link in bio). If you don’t have the cookbook yet, swipe left to give this recipe a try!

Gerber recommends Lil’ Crunchies to babies who are only 8 months old. My son is now around this age, and I can’t imagine feeding him Cheetos, and that is basically what these are.

It saddens me when I see that these are still one of the “best selling” toddler foods at Target...so they must be pretty popular. 

Here’s why Lil’ Crunchies are a horrible idea:

✔️ They have almost identical ingredients to Simply Cheetos. Common sense should tell you that babies don’t need Cheetos in their life. 

✔️ They contain “Autolyzed Yeast Extract” to get kids hooked on them, which is an ingredient that contains the same main component of MSG. 

✔️ They have no real nutritional value, and children should get their nutrients from real food.

✔️ When very young children eat processed foods they are reinforcing a love for heavily processed foods that come out of box instead of for real food.

✔️ A big reason some kids don’t seem to like vegetables is because they are not nurtured to like the flavor and bitterness of them from a young age. Babies need to be exposed to vegetables on a regular basis to learn to love them, and that shouldn’t be crowded out by Cheetos.

And it’s not just Lil’ Crunchies. Many toddler snacks and puffs are primarily unhealthy processed flour, sugar, and not real food either.

It’s no wonder many kids don’t like vegetables. Their taste buds are being hijacked by products like this! 

Click the link in my bio to see what a typical day of feeding a toddler looks like in my house, and you won’t find any Cheetos on the menu 😉

Please share this with all the parents you know!

When I first shared this graphic a few months ago, Ghirardelli was using the risky ingredient TBHQ in their chocolate squares. Well, I’m excited to let you know that they have quietly replaced TBHQ with “extracts of oregano, flaxseed, plum, and green tea”. Swipe left to see the new ingredient list.

Yeah! Thank you to everyone in the #FoodBabeArmy who has asked these companies to remove TBHQ. 

This is one ingredient that we need out of our food ASAP.

TBHQ is a synthetic preservative still found in many of the most popular foods here in America…like Pop Tarts, Cheez-it Crackers, and Reese’s Peanut Butter Cups. Foods that many children eat often!

A peer-reviewed study by the Environmental Working Group found TBHQ may harm the immune system.

TBHQ has already been shown to worsen flu symptoms and is linked to other health issues, such as increasing the risk of food allergies to nuts, milk, eggs, wheat, and shellfish.

Although the FDA allows food companies to use this controversial preservative, it’s banned in some other countries, and you rarely see it used in Europe.

When new research comes out like this, the FDA does nothing! They don’t reevaluate or pull ingredients from our food supply. 

It’s up to us...

It’s up to us to protect ourselves by refusing to buy products with TBHQ on the ingredient list and demanding that these companies stop using potentially harmful substances. 

Both Chick-Fil-A and McDonald’s used to use TBHQ in their food - but after customers raised concerns they both ditched it completely. Now Ghirardelli has gotten on board too. 

Let’s get everyone else to do the same!

If making sweeping changes to your diet is hard, here’s one thing that you can commit to doing every day that will make a huge difference – it’s fast and easy, and something I do every day…
 
Drink a green smoothie every day! Swipe left for 4 recipes to start.
 
A simple green smoothie is the best fast food available and a superb way to add more veggies to your diet. I’ve found, too, that this alleviates food cravings because it provides a burst of nutrition – one that’s not usually present in the typical American diet. 
 
When your body doesn’t get what it needs nutritionally speaking, cravings kick in. And if you give in to those cravings, you’re on the road to gaining weight. Once you start to pump your body with greens, you’ll start craving them instead!
